ent of the\ndisc through continued star-formation. For cluster discs, the perturbation is\nimpulsive tidal shocking at pericentres and not tidal stripping of outer disc\nstellar material, whereas for control discs, a combination of mergers and AGN\nfeedback appears to be the key driving force behind morphological\ntransformations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Apr 2020 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 8 Apr 2020 16:40:41 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 14 Jul 2020 14:24:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-15"}
